#compdef nba-go
# =============================================================================
# nba-go — Homer Chen's "The finest NBA CLI" — a Node.js CLI
#          for browsing live + historical NBA player statistics,
#          box scores, game schedules, and play-by-play in the
#          terminal.  Distinguishing from other sports-data CLIs
#          (football-cli, soccer-go, mlb-cli) by:
#            - LIVE PLAY-BY-PLAY: real-time game scoreboard
#              + per-possession play-by-play feed in a blessed
#              TUI panel
#            - PLAYER CAREER STATS: regular season + playoffs
#              + biographical info via NBA's official stats API
#            - MULTI-PLAYER COMPARISON: side-by-side stats
#              tables for arbitrary lists of players
#            - GAME SCHEDULE by date (yesterday/today/tomorrow/
#              explicit-date) with TV-network metadata
#            - cli-table3 RENDERING: every box-score, stats
#              line, and comparison panel rendered through
#              cli-table3's wide-character-aware + ANSI-color-
#              aware table layout engine
#            - INTERACTIVE GAME SELECTOR via inquirer prompts
#              + blessed TUI for live games
#            - cfonts BIG TEXT banners for branding (nba-go's
#              startup banner uses cfonts)
#          Used by: NBA fans who want terminal-native stats
#          browsing, developers learning Node.js CLI patterns,
#          and as a reference implementation for "rich
#          terminal output via cli-table3 + blessed + inquirer".
#
# Author:  Homer Chen (xxhomey19 / homerchen19 on GitHub) —
#          Taiwanese full-stack engineer who released nba-go
#          in 2017 as a personal-project NBA stats CLI.
#          Project is in maintenance mode (last release 0.4.0)
#          but core functionality remains operational against
#          NBA's public stats endpoints.
# Source:  https://github.com/homerchen19/nba-go
#          https://github.com/homerchen19/nba-go/blob/master/src/cli.js
#          https://github.com/homerchen19/nba-go/blob/master/src/command/player/
#          https://github.com/homerchen19/nba-go/blob/master/src/command/game/
# CLI:     src/cli.js — commander.js-based subcommand tree
#          with two subcommands (`player <name>` aliased `p`,
#          `game` aliased `g`) + per-subcommand short/long
#          flags + `.on('--help', ...)` custom help text.
#          Headline library: cli-table3 (commander is well-
#          documented across many Node completions — cli-table3
#          is the new variant being documented here).
# Library: cli-table3 (https://github.com/cli-table/cli-table3)
#          ("cli-table3" — community fork chain:
#           Automattic/cli-table (2012, abandoned) →
#           jamestalmage/cli-table2 (2015, abandoned) →
#           cli-table/cli-table3 (2018+, active).  The
#           DEFINITIVE Node.js ASCII/Unicode table renderer
#           for terminal output.  Distinct from `table` (npm),
#           `text-table`, `as-table`, `ascii-table`, and `console.
#           table` (Node stdlib) by being:
#             1. WIDE-CHARACTER aware (handles CJK / emoji /
#                wcwidth-2 cells correctly for column alignment)
#             2. ANSI-COLOR aware (uses string-width / strip-ansi
#                to compute visible width separately from raw
#                length — colored cells align correctly)
#             3. STREAMING + CROSS-CELL alignment (rows added
#                via push() reflow column widths)
#             4. NESTED tables (cells can contain sub-tables;
#                widths compute recursively)
#             5. COLSPAN + ROWSPAN cell-merging via { content:
#                ..., colSpan: n, rowSpan: m } cell objects
#             6. HORIZONTAL + VERTICAL alignment per cell + per
#                column via { hAlign: 'left'|'center'|'right',
#                vAlign: 'top'|'center'|'bottom' }
#             7. UNICODE BOX-DRAWING (lookup table swaps
#                top/mid/bottom/left/right/inner chars for any
#                style: single-line, double-line, rounded,
#                no-borders, custom)
#             8. PER-CELL STYLE TUNING via chars option for
#                conditional formatting.)
# License: MIT (nba-go); MIT (cli-table3)
# Status:  nba-go — 3,700+ stars on homerchen19/nba-go, top-
#          starred Node CLI in the "sports data" niche;
#          cli-table3 — 660+ stars on cli-table/cli-table3,
#          ~70M weekly npm downloads, foundational dependency
#          of nba-go + autocannon + nativescript-cli + cron-
#          parser + hardhat-gas-reporter + migrate-mongo +
#          1500+ Node.js CLIs that produce tabular output.
#
